Introduction

Jeon Minju (전민주) is a South Korean singer. She was a contestant on K-Pop Star 2 and K-Pop Star 6. She debuted as a soloist in 2014 with the digital single "Goodbye Rain." In 2015, she debuted as a member of the now-disbanded group The Ark and pre-debut group Dayday.

In 2019, Minju and Euna Kim debuted as the duo Khan. However, they disbanded shortly after.
